snippet.textDisplay:
....this is what dancing is now...?
These are just fast jerky movements with random slow parts. Really doubt she can do the same dance exactly the same every time.
A lot of these moves aren't new and weren't created by the people referenced in the description box; and yet she's just doing adequate recreations. Her movements are stiff. Example? She's done a lot of moves that are supposed to make it look like you have no joints, like that "Git Up" one where she does the hinged arm thing that you've seen everywhere for years. You know which one I'm talking about, people do robot dances and when they "turn off", they dangle their arm like it's on a hinge slowing down.
And why does she have to have that stupid grin on her face the entire time? Not something you see dancers do, not even the little kids that go on America's Got Talent just for the fun of dancing on TV. You can pause the video at any point while she's "dancing" and her face will be exactly the same. It's like she's wearing a mask.
Only thing that made sense was when she flapped her arms like a chicken during the Skeleton "dance". Obviously not because chickens and skeletons have anything in common, but because her nose makes her look like a bird.
"Wowwww, fast music plays and she starts dancing.... **faster**?? Oh my god, I didn't see that coming! I thought she was gonna dance slower!"
